00:18:51.250 --> 00:18:54.690
The key point is that the
mimetic muscles are found only

00:18:54.690 --> 00:18:55.990
in the mammals.

00:18:55.990 --> 00:18:58.800 position:56%
And that's why the other vertebrates
aren't near as expressive.

00:18:58.800 --> 00:19:03.440
They don't have the capacity to
move their skin on their faces,

00:19:03.440 --> 00:19:07.770
in the way that we mammals do
with these mimetic muscles.

00:19:07.770 --> 00:19:11.080
The face is the only
place on the mammal's body

00:19:11.080 --> 00:19:14.550
where there's a direct connection
to the skin for moving the skin.

00:19:14.550 --> 00:19:17.260
Okay. And it's a mammalian
specialty.

00:19:17.260 --> 00:19:22.790
