indeed, more humanlike than this,

00:32:39.240 --> 00:32:43.830
which looks more like
a typical mammal.

00:32:43.830 --> 00:32:49.220 position:56%
So, the first major set of changes
took place roughly 50 million years,

00:32:49.220 --> 00:32:53.910
ago, changes that led in the
direction of the human face.

00:32:53.910 --> 00:32:59.270
And the second phase of
major changes leading

00:32:59.270 --> 00:33:03.390
to modern human face, including
ultimately anatomically modern

00:33:03.390 --> 00:33:06.020
humans, shown here by this figure.

00:33:06.020 --> 00:33:08.090
Took place much later.

00:33:08.090 --> 00:33:13.700
Roughly starting about four
to 6 million years, ago.

00:33:13.700 --> 00:33:17.380
And here, I've just
sketched it very crudely.

00:33:17.380 --> 00:33:23.190
Now, we don't know what the
